      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNAKE OIL (9) backs up after overcoming a wide barrier to score by 2.2 metres at this circuit and distance on Tuesday. Should enjoy a pretty soft run from this draw and with the sprint lane in play he could strike again. RUDIMENTARY (2) followed a Canberra win with a placing from the back row last start. Yet to miss a place at this circuit and distance and draws well. SINBAD SASSY (8) resumes from a spell of six-and-a-half months after closing off last campaign in good form, putting together a string of top-two results at this venue. Must overcome a wide draw but was readied with a nice trial and is yet to miss a place when fresh. DONNIE MAC (6) won by close to 10m here two back before sticking on for second last time. Has the speed to go forward so can be prominent again. BULLETIN (7) draws wider but must be respected after toughing out a win at this circuit and distance last week.",
